00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:42,060
=Twin Fire Dawn=

2
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:45,060
=Episode 3=

3
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:47,180
You people who studied abroad

4
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:49,900
really are quite open minded.

5
00:00:52,580 --> 00:00:53,980
Stop avoiding the question.

6
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:55,900
Tell me.

7
00:00:57,580 --> 00:00:59,140
Why did you pull a knife on me?

8
00:01:01,260 --> 00:01:02,740
It's because

9
00:01:03,060 --> 00:01:04,940
we had never met before.

10
00:01:05,060 --> 00:01:07,700
We only met yesterday, and we
were already expected to share a bed.

11
00:01:07,940 --> 00:01:09,740
I wasn't ready for it.

12
00:01:10,460 --> 00:01:12,060
As for the spiked wine,

13
00:01:12,180 --> 00:01:14,260
my brother said money
can't compare to power.

14
00:01:14,580 --> 00:01:16,700
The Xue family
will still need your support.

15
00:01:16,940 --> 00:01:18,540
He told me to win your favor.

16
00:01:34,020 --> 00:01:35,020
Commander,

17
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:38,140
don't be upset.

18
00:01:47,420 --> 00:01:50,259
Last night, Young Lady Xue
was pointing a knife at me.

19
00:01:50,260 --> 00:01:51,740
And now,

20
00:01:52,140 --> 00:01:53,780
you're suddenly
acting so warm and eager.

21
00:01:55,460 --> 00:01:56,860
That's because

22
00:01:58,020 --> 00:01:59,299
after seeing you up close

23
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:01,540
and admiring your charm,

24
00:02:01,820 --> 00:02:04,980
I've completely fallen for you.

25
00:02:05,620 --> 00:02:06,620
Commander,

26
00:02:07,140 --> 00:02:09,060
can you give me one more chance

27
00:02:09,620 --> 00:02:11,700
to make up for last night?

28
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:36,540
What a pity.

29
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:39,260
I'm not interested in you.

30
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:44,420
If you're not interested,
why did you marry me?

31
00:02:45,380 --> 00:02:46,580
(That's right.)

32
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:49,700
(Gu Nianchi, you've married your enemy.)

33
00:02:51,460 --> 00:02:54,020
Everyone in Yancheng knows
the Xue family is the wealthiest.

34
00:02:54,220 --> 00:02:55,540
This marriage between us

35
00:02:56,340 --> 00:02:58,300
is nothing more than
a deal of power and money.

36
00:02:59,020 --> 00:02:59,980
Is that all?

37
00:03:00,340 --> 00:03:01,900
I'm still young.

38
00:03:01,940 --> 00:03:04,820
Just because of a family arrangement,
do I have to waste my whole life here?

39
00:03:06,580 --> 00:03:07,660
Let me tell you something.

40
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:09,460
Before I married you,

41
00:03:09,620 --> 00:03:10,740
there was someone I loved.

42
00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:13,700
And we promised we'd
grow old with the one we loved.

43
00:03:14,540 --> 00:03:15,780
It's just a pity.

44
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:21,500
After spending all that time together,

45
00:03:22,180 --> 00:03:23,300
I think

46
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:25,820
you already understood my feelings.

47
00:03:27,260 --> 00:03:28,860
Why are you telling me this?

48
00:03:29,260 --> 00:03:30,580
I'm trying to tell you this.

49
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:32,980
I'll remember the Zhuang family
of North City.

50
00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:33,940
Don't worry.

51
00:03:34,420 --> 00:03:35,860
Once my eyes recover,

52
00:03:36,060 --> 00:03:37,740
I'll come to your home and marry you.

53
00:03:39,580 --> 00:03:40,700
Commander,

54
00:03:42,660 --> 00:03:44,580
have you ever loved someone before?

55
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,460
That's none of your business.

56
00:04:23,820 --> 00:04:24,740
Xinran.

57
00:04:26,940 --> 00:04:27,940
What is it?

58
00:04:28,060 --> 00:04:28,860
Come here.

59
00:04:29,180 --> 00:04:30,380
I need to ask you something.

60
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:35,740
You brought that wine

61
00:04:36,260 --> 00:04:37,820
into my room yesterday, didn't you?

62
00:04:38,940 --> 00:04:40,140
So what if I did?

63
00:04:40,660 --> 00:04:42,340
I'm not here to serve you.

64
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,580
Young Master Xue told me to do it.

65
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:45,820
I only listen to him.

66
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:49,500
So the spiked wine really was
Young Master Xue's idea.

67
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:51,380
What did you say?

68
00:04:52,060 --> 00:04:53,380
The spiked wine?

69
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:54,980
Shameless.

70
00:04:55,260 --> 00:04:57,459
You're the one who sent
that spiked wine to my room.

71
00:04:57,460 --> 00:04:58,820
And who's the shameless one here?

72
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:00,059
I...

73
00:05:00,060 --> 00:05:00,819
And

74
00:05:00,820 --> 00:05:01,860
another thing.

75
00:05:02,780 --> 00:05:04,339
Since you're working for him,

76
00:05:04,340 --> 00:05:06,219
you should know what he wants to see.

77
00:05:06,220 --> 00:05:07,820
You'd better behave yourself.

78
00:05:08,060 --> 00:05:08,860
Otherwise,

79
00:05:09,020 --> 00:05:10,620
neither of us will end well.

80
00:05:19,980 --> 00:05:23,539
♪How can broken love ever go on?♪

81
00:05:23,540 --> 00:05:25,579
(I'll remember the Zhuang family
of North City.)

82
00:05:25,580 --> 00:05:26,540
(Don't worry.)

83
00:05:27,060 --> 00:05:28,260
(Once my eyes recover,)

84
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:30,380
(I'll come to your home and marry you.)

85
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:34,659
♪In the blink of an eye,
everything falls apart♪

86
00:05:34,660 --> 00:05:36,199
(I never forgot that promise.)

87
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:38,179
♪Bound by the fate we cannot escape♪

88
00:05:38,180 --> 00:05:39,380
(It's just a pity.)

89
00:05:39,660 --> 00:05:40,780
(The place remains,)

90
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:43,660
(but the person is gone.)

91
00:05:45,150 --> 00:05:49,589
♪Fragile hearts can hardly bear goodbye♪

92
00:05:49,590 --> 00:05:51,440
(Place Hotel)

93
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:03,980
Thank you.

94
00:06:08,620 --> 00:06:09,419
How did it go?

95
00:06:09,420 --> 00:06:10,800
Did Xue Tian give you a hard time?

96
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:12,180
No.

97
00:06:12,460 --> 00:06:14,660
He found me
at the newspaper office the next day.

98
00:06:14,900 --> 00:06:16,219
But what's done is done.

99
00:06:16,220 --> 00:06:17,740
There was nothing he could do about it.

100
00:06:18,140 --> 00:06:18,940
By the way,

101
00:06:19,060 --> 00:06:21,300
did Gu Nianchi suspect anything?

102
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:23,539
Everything's fine on my side.

103
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:24,380
Don't worry.

104
00:06:26,060 --> 00:06:27,059
Anyway,

105
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:28,340
be careful.

106
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:29,659
And don't forget.

107
00:06:29,660 --> 00:06:30,819
Only by finding evidence

108
00:06:30,820 --> 00:06:32,900
can we bring Gu Nianchi to justice.

109
00:06:32,940 --> 00:06:34,819
That way, you won't be blamed

110
00:06:34,820 --> 00:06:36,099
for marrying in my place.

111
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:38,180
And it won't affect
my brother's business.

112
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:41,780
Trust me. I'll definitely find evidence
of Gu Nianchi's crimes.

113
00:06:42,060 --> 00:06:44,540
When the time comes,
I'll still need your help. Help me expose him.

114
00:06:44,820 --> 00:06:45,660
Of course.

115
00:07:09,340 --> 00:07:11,020
Playing alone must be boring.

116
00:07:19,220 --> 00:07:20,780
I'll play with you.

117
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:29,380
The white ball is the beginning.

118
00:07:29,460 --> 00:07:30,980
The black ball is the end.

119
00:07:37,860 --> 00:07:39,500
I only play straight shots.

120
00:07:40,940 --> 00:07:42,019
I wonder

121
00:07:42,020 --> 00:07:44,100
if I can shoot my way into your heart.

122
00:07:50,940 --> 00:07:52,940
You really did study abroad.

123
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:54,860
You sure know a lot of tricks.

124
00:08:05,340 --> 00:08:06,180
Your turn.

125
00:08:36,180 --> 00:08:37,460
In that case,

126
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:42,540
let me make things
a little more challenging for you.

127
00:09:01,980 --> 00:09:03,580
Don't try these little tricks on me.

128
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:04,820
I don't like them.

129
00:09:36,180 --> 00:09:37,900
(The water's been drugged by me.)

130
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:40,320
(Once you soak in it,
the poison will seep into your bones.)

131
00:09:40,380 --> 00:09:41,540
(This time,)

132
00:09:41,660 --> 00:09:43,380
(I won't let you escape again.)

133
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:54,059
You've worked hard today.

134
00:09:54,060 --> 00:09:55,940
Why not take a bath and relax?

135
00:09:56,260 --> 00:09:57,620
Is the water not warm enough?

136
00:09:58,620 --> 00:10:00,140
I'll add some hot water for you.

137
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:03,180
Alright.

138
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:09,740
If the water temperature isn't right,
then perhaps my wife will do instead.

139
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:15,540
So you were waiting for me.

140
00:10:15,940 --> 00:10:17,380
Why didn't you say earlier?

141
00:10:18,540 --> 00:10:19,740
Then let me

142
00:10:21,380 --> 00:10:23,100
bathe you myself.

143
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:35,620
What a coincidence.

144
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:37,820
I've already bathed.

145
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:41,860
Then let me join you one more time.

146
00:10:59,380 --> 00:11:00,700
You'd better be careful.

147
00:11:01,780 --> 00:11:03,100
If you fall in,

148
00:11:03,780 --> 00:11:06,140
you'll be in trouble.

149
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:14,780
Thank you, Commander.

150
00:11:16,180 --> 00:11:19,300
The water temperature isn't right,
make yourself comfortable, then.

151
00:11:20,740 --> 00:11:21,939
(You think I don't know)

152
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:23,460
(what you put in the water?)

153
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:26,540
(I'd like to see
what exactly you're planning.)

154
00:11:31,260 --> 00:11:33,099
(You're even harder to deal with)

155
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:34,660
(than I expected.)

156
00:11:46,740 --> 00:11:47,500
Commander.

157
00:12:09,420 --> 00:12:10,180
Darling.

158
00:12:15,340 --> 00:12:16,459
Didn't you just

159
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:17,540
go upstairs?

160
00:12:18,780 --> 00:12:21,140
You must've mistaken someone else.
That was Cheng Yi.

161
00:12:22,620 --> 00:12:23,260
Oh.

162
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:25,339
And that room upstairs...

163
00:12:25,340 --> 00:12:26,820
It's just an ordinary room.

164
00:12:27,020 --> 00:12:29,420
Cheng Yi rests there
sometimes while on duty.

165
00:12:33,660 --> 00:12:34,540
How about

166
00:12:36,220 --> 00:12:37,420
we go eat steak?

167
00:12:41,140 --> 00:12:42,380
Now?

168
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:43,220
Right now.

169
00:12:45,540 --> 00:12:46,659
Then wait for me.

170
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:48,099
I'll go get changed first.

171
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:49,740
No need. Let's go.

172
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:51,140
You...

173
00:13:03,420 --> 00:13:05,820
Why did you suddenly
want to treat me to steak?

174
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,600
I just suddenly felt like eating it.

175
00:13:10,140 --> 00:13:11,540
Then I'll make it for you next time.

176
00:13:11,820 --> 00:13:12,780
Nianchi.

177
00:13:15,740 --> 00:13:17,260
Call me Commander.

178
00:13:18,300 --> 00:13:19,940
Calling you Commander feels too distant.

179
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:22,220
Don't you want us
to get closer sooner?

180
00:13:24,820 --> 00:13:25,900
I told you.

181
00:13:26,580 --> 00:13:28,180
Call me Commander.

182
00:13:29,860 --> 00:13:30,980
Alright.

183
00:13:31,740 --> 00:13:32,860
Here, Commander.

184
00:13:40,180 --> 00:13:42,380
This medium rare steak is too bloody.

185
00:13:43,020 --> 00:13:44,140
I don't like it.

186
00:13:48,340 --> 00:13:51,340
You're really hard to read.

187
00:13:51,380 --> 00:13:52,619
Your moods shift without warning.

188
00:13:52,620 --> 00:13:55,040
- No one can predict your temper.
- Then stay away from me.

189
00:13:56,420 --> 00:13:58,219
But I happen to like men like you.

190
00:13:58,220 --> 00:13:59,539
Mysterious men

191
00:13:59,540 --> 00:14:00,660
are the most charming.

192
00:14:05,020 --> 00:14:08,620
You asked me over to eat steak,
but you're not even going to feed me?

193
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:33,500
Thank you, Commander.

194
00:14:36,660 --> 00:14:37,540
Commander,

195
00:14:38,180 --> 00:14:40,460
how about we go see a movie tonight?

196
00:14:40,740 --> 00:14:42,340
I'm afraid you'll be disappointed.

197
00:14:42,460 --> 00:14:43,660
I already have plans tonight.

198
00:14:45,220 --> 00:14:47,780
Who's more important
than your newlywed wife?

199
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:50,060
Some singer from "Golden Love Songs,"

200
00:14:50,660 --> 00:14:52,420
or a dancer from Paramount?

201
00:14:56,300 --> 00:14:57,820
You really

202
00:14:58,180 --> 00:15:00,540
do know me well.

203
00:15:02,220 --> 00:15:03,340
Of course.

204
00:15:43,740 --> 00:15:44,700
You're here.

205
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:52,810
♪How can broken love ever go on?♪

206
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:59,440
♪How much hope must fade into despair?♪

207
00:15:59,940 --> 00:16:03,520
♪In the blink of an eye,
everything falls apart♪

208
00:16:03,860 --> 00:16:06,870
♪Bound by the fate we cannot escape♪

209
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:12,160
♪You and I caught in
this tangled love and hate♪

210
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:18,470
♪Fragile hearts can hardly bear goodbye♪

211
00:16:19,530 --> 00:16:25,130
♪How many times
must pain cut deep before we wake?♪

212
00:16:25,670 --> 00:16:29,050
♪I once gave myself
to you so completely♪

213
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:32,249
♪Still holding on to that heart♪

214
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:37,389
♪Only to suffer your fatal blow♪

215
00:16:37,390 --> 00:16:41,709
♪How desperately
I long to hold you close♪

216
00:16:41,710 --> 00:16:44,289
♪Yet I approach you with such caution♪

217
00:16:44,290 --> 00:16:46,569
♪How could a stand in ever have♪

218
00:16:46,570 --> 00:16:50,119
♪The right to be loved by you?♪

219
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:54,649
♪If love is nothing
more than endless schemes♪

220
00:16:54,650 --> 00:16:57,180
♪Used and abandoned in the end♪

221
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:59,269
♪Still I walk into♪

222
00:16:59,270 --> 00:17:02,869
♪The trap you set without regret♪

223
00:17:02,870 --> 00:17:06,919
♪How desperately
I long to hold you close♪

224
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:09,499
♪Yet keep it buried deep inside♪

225
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,659
♪A stand in can never cross♪

226
00:17:11,660 --> 00:17:15,099
♪The shortest distance between us♪

227
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:20,070
♪If love can
make someone lose themselves♪

228
00:17:20,230 --> 00:17:24,900
♪Then let me stay by your side♪

229
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:29,249
♪A substitute♪

230
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:34,250
♪Needs no reason♪

